Package: irods-fish
Version: 0.2.3-1
Section: misc
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Depends: fish (>= 2.7), irods-icommands
Maintainer: Tony Edgin <tedgin@cyverse.org>
Description: fish support for iRODS
 Being able to switch between iRODS zones is useful for someone who works in
 multiple zones. For users of fish, this package provides commands that simplify
 working in multiple zones or, more generally, with multiple iRODS environments.
 It also provides of a port Bruno Bzeznik's bash tab completions for iRODS to
 fish.
